{"id": "general-chat--development--the-meshcore-analyzer-is-very-cool-i", "title": "The meshcore analyzer is very cool. I", "forum": "General Chat", "messages": [{"id": "1459103616714670110", "author": "Seacourt", "author_handle": "bb293301", "user_id": "1066375624438071417", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, January 9, 2026 3:36 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-09 3:36 a.m.", "text": "", "content_html": "", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1459229752022794414", "author": "treehouse ⚡", "author_handle": "reginald000", "user_id": "397934763555684355", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/397934763555684355/a_4cbd779361ecd6dd23aa52270607fe9d.gif?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, January 9, 2026 11:58 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-09 11:58 a.m.", "text": "You may want to have a peek at pyMC Console. It’s a network analytic focused approach built on top of Repeater and Core. It would be great to get your thoughts! I’m very much an enthusiast here, and would love an expert opinion on how we can improve the visualizations and backend computations", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>You may want to have a peek at pyMC Console. It’s a network analytic focused approach built on top of Repeater and Core. It would be great to get your thoughts! I’m very much an enthusiast here, and would love an expert opinion on how we can improve the visualizations and backend computations</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1459103163494695125/1459229751742042296/image0.jpg?ex=69ec49db&amp;is=69eaf85b&amp;hm=2d16014033cfa3a914d9d36917652ac9b7fc819cf3fbf23884e8eecb3ebebb79&amp;\"> <img class=chatlog__attachment-media src=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1459103163494695125/1459229751742042296/image0.jpg?ex=69ec49db&amp;is=69eaf85b&amp;hm=2d16014033cfa3a914d9d36917652ac9b7fc819cf3fbf23884e8eecb3ebebb79&amp;\" alt=\"Image attachment\" title=\"Image: image0.jpg (291.64 KB)\" loading=lazy> </a></div>"], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1459231036251570347", "author": "Seacourt", "author_handle": "bb293301", "user_id": "1066375624438071417", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, January 9, 2026 12:03 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-09 12:03 p.m.", "text": "Very nice. Do you use viterbi to choose the max likelihood paths?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Very nice. Do you use viterbi to choose the max likelihood paths?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1459231069856337952", "author": "treehouse ⚡", "author_handle": "reginald000", "user_id": "397934763555684355", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/397934763555684355/a_4cbd779361ecd6dd23aa52270607fe9d.gif?size=512", "timestamp": "Friday, January 9, 2026 12:03 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-01-09 12:03 p.m.", "text": "Rough POC using the topology data merged with low res topography tiles to create a very rudimentary first draft of known repeater “coverage” (coverage being used very lightly here)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Rough POC using the topology data merged with low res topography tiles to create a very rudimentary first draft of known repeater “coverage” (coverage being used very lightly here)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": ["<div class=chatlog__attachment><a href=\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1459103163494695125/1459231069588160522/image.png?ex=69ec4b16&amp;is=69eaf996&amp;hm=69c8faf99c42e2009a22e98d422aff6cf91cc1ca73238bc8cfe41ec0fa8a6d9e&amp;\"> <img class=chatlog__attachment-media src=\"https://cdn.